After breaking my back in 2018 in a similar crash (rock into spine), I learned the hard way to wear a back protector. My back was completely fine after this crash wearing the @leatt_mtb Airflex back protector. Fortunately, I only had a bruised knee needing an x-ray.

I wear the Airflex any time I’m doing something gnarly, and has saved me on more than one occasion. Get yours at @competitivecyclist! Link in story ⛑️

This year, no good deed goes unnoticed 🙌🏼 The Chevrolet Good Deeds cup is back for its 7th Season! From January 20th to March 4th, Chevrolet is challenging minor hockey teams across the country to do as many good deeds as they can to fill the cup. Whichever team does the most good deeds can win $100K for charity! 🤑

To enter: record yourself doing good deeds, upload those deeds to any social platform, tag @chevroletcanada and use #GoodDeedsCup and #Contest, plus mention your team’s name. Use the link in my bio for more information! #GoodDeedsCup #FillTheCup #Sponsored #Ad

Flying can be expensive, but it doesn’t have to be. I bought my Cessna 170 for less than most used trucks, and @air101channel insurance is making it affordable & attainable for new pilots to get in the air. As a low-time pilot myself, my premiums are similar to what I pay in vehicle insurance. Like all passions, don’t let $ be the reason not to try something 🙌🏼✈️ Always a way to make it happen if you want something enough.

7 years of riding my @giantbicycles Glory Advanced has come to an end 🛐🫡 This bike has been an integral part of my career from film shoots, Rampages and countless bike park & shuttle laps. 

I put thousands of hours on these Glory’s, and never even broke a linkage bolt. This is an outstanding testament for the sheer quality of Giant’s manufacturing & bicycles across the board. 

Building up my new 2023 Glory Advanced as we speak, and PUMPED for the new whip and where it will take me. 

Thank you to my entire Giant family for building such incredible, quality & lasting bikes 🙏🏻👨🏻‍🔧
